Arsenal star, Ben White, has named teammate Takehiro Tomiyasu as the best right-back he’s played with. White said that Tomiyasu does simple things at a world-class level, adding that he is amazing. Tomiyasu joined Arsenal from Bologna last summer transfer window for £15.5 million. The Japan international has impressed in his first few months at the Gunners. He has already cemented his place as Mikel Arteta’s first-choice right-back. “Tomi is amazing. He’s the best right-back I have ever played with. “He’s always focused. It’s an honour to play next to him. “Tomi does the simple things at a world-class level. He is very alert and he isn’t careless in games. “From the beginning, he’s completely understood English and speaks as well as I do,” White told DAZN Japan.